# Permanent Guardrails

Apply in every runtime and protocol. Details in `docs/control/PROFILE.md` and `docs/ENGINEERING_STANDARDS.md`.

## Product and data

- No legacy support or obsolete fallbacks.
- No productive hardcodes by SKU, page, or one-off catalog row.
- SKU/page literals only in tests, fixtures, audits, or evidence.
- Do not mix importer batches.
- Do not optimize one FDL page by degrading the full 65-page seed.

## IMPORT-FDL (when task touches importer/parser/grouping)

Every applicable task separates:

- Focus page(s)
- Regression pages: **11, 12, 13, 14**
- Full catalog gate: **65 pages**

Track: `rows_importable`, `rows_blocked`, `masters_created`, `variants_created`, `price_entries`, `catalog_items_created`, false mega-families, category contamination.

`variants_created == price_entries == catalog_items_created` must hold unless explicitly justified.

## Agent ownership

Use `docs/control/AGENT_REGISTRY.yaml`. Do not edit outside assigned agent scope. Agent 2A and Agent 2B never run concurrently.

## Paused work

Do not reactivate paused workstreams unless the user explicitly instructs.

## Frontend (when applicable)

Validate responsive behavior, accessibility, loading/error/empty states; browser QA for significant visual changes when environment allows.

## Authority

Live state and registries override historical docs. User instruction overrides docs when explicit. Never infer decisions or close QA-pending work.
